Overview
Coordinates and supports door-door international moving services by Hilldrup in support of a variety of client groups. Monitors the move progression while also maintaining direct contact with customers through key touch points such as the pre-move survey, loading and delivery of their shipment.
Position Scope
Works directly with the Team Leader. Provides quality service to both internal and external clients. Frequent contact with direct customers, agent partners and Hilldrup local dispatch. Serves as a single point of contact for the customers’ origin or destination services.
Significant Responsibilities and Essential Functions
Reviews initial order from Hilldrup client and contacts the transferring employee within four (4) business hours;
Responsible for electronic registration for assigned international shipments, into the Hilldrup system. Monitors shipments through the move management system and regularly inputs status updates;
Reviews all customs regulations and informs the customers of all necessary regulations, paperwork/documentation required for an international relocation;
Ensures that shipments are routed via quoted services and that all charges are correct by reviewing all invoices submitted by carriers;
Responsible for frequent communications with the customer throughout the relocation in order to maintain a high quality of customer service;
Responsible for achieving adequate profit per order and minimizing potential loss;
Schedules pre-move surveys as appropriate;
Compiles quotes based on survey results using published and/or spot international rates for household goods and POV shipments worldwide;
Sets up third party services as requested;
Works with Hilldrup local dispatch on a daily basis in confirming the scheduling of shipments;
Places calls to transferee on pack/load day and/or delivery day to ensure Hilldrup is meeting all customer needs;
Follows up on any service issues and escalates to management when needed;
Ability to manage deadlines and consistently work a strong caseload;
Provides accounting department with billing data including door-door rate information and charges, including accessorial costs when applicable;
Responsible for developing and maintaining strong working relationship with Hilldrup service partners.

Minimum Job Qualifications Required
Bachelor’s or Associates degree preferred, and/or equivalent business experience.
Two to four years of transportation related experience, including customer service;
Ability to read and speak the English language;
Effective analytical decision-making;
Excellent verbal/written communications skills;
Demonstrates pro-active approach to problem resolution;
Strong working knowledge of Microsoft Office applications;
Bi-lingual is a plus.

Incumbents will be expected to embrace and champion Hilldrup’s organizational competencies/values;
Empowered Accountability
Fearless Communication
Infectious Positivity
Purposeful Agility
Uncompromised Integrity
Unwavering Commitment

Keen to become part of a truly global, collaborative team of professionals? Your journey begins here.
SUMMARY
Under the supervision and support of the Supervisor and the Manager of the New Business Conflicts division of the Conflicts and Compliance Department, this position is responsible for gathering, maintaining and filing information related to the firm’s compliance with various laws, regulations, and policies, including: state and Federal compliance disclosures, including Lobbying Disclosure Act (LDA), Foreign Agent Registration Act (FARA) and other similar filings and disclosures. The position will report to the Compliance Manager and may receive guidance from lawyers in relevant firm practices. To the extent that time is available, this position will support other compliance and risk management responsibilities.
JOB DESCRIPTION
Assist in the review and filing process of registrations and periodic compliance reports (LD-1, LD-2, LD-203) submitted to the House and Senate Clerk’s Offices. Review and research the requirements associated with the LD-1, LD-2, and LD-203 forms as necessary in order to support firm lawyers and assistants in preparing quarterly and bi-annual filings;
Understand and utilize the firm's lobbying disclosure database and other computerized databases as needed;
Maintain and update the lobbying database and other lobbying related spreadsheets and reports;
Maintain records of compliance activities for audits related to LDA and FARA compliance;
Assist in the preparation of templates, checklists, FAQs, process instructions, and best practice documents related to LDA and FARA Compliance;
Conduct compliance monitoring as assigned to verify adherence with firm policies and procedures and applicable laws and regulations;
Review and research the requirements associated with FARA Registration forms, amendments, exhibits and summary reports in order to support firm lawyers and assistants in compiling periodic and ad hoc filings;
Maintain firm compliance procedural documents, update documents with any new changes;
Other duties as assigned.
REQUIRED SKILLS
Strong attention to detail and problem solving skills. Strong research, analysis, and communication skills required. Strong organizational skills and ability to balance multiple priorities required. Must possess a self-starter attitude and be able to thrive in a collegial, team-oriented atmosphere. Must be responsible for meeting deadlines under very tight time constraints and many other demands. Candidate must be able to grasp quickly the details of a wide variety of compliance-related issues. Must have strong Microsoft Word and Excel skills.
EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE
Bachelor’s degree, preferably in political science, or humanities field
Minimum 1-2 years’ experience in a compliance/legal role conducting compliance reviews
